description:
&lt;p&gt;East Sussex ADHD Team&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are establishing a new cross county ADHD Service and we are recruiting  1WTE Band 4 nurse associate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are also recruiting for administrative support to the team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicants will join an already established team of 7 nurses and will be managed day to day by a Band 7 Team Leader.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you interested in joining this new and exciting team?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be expected to provide an ADHD service to all young people referred to CAMHS for assessment of ADHD&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will participate in screening neuro-developmental packs, assessing and using the QB testing tool and in reviews.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There will be opportunities for development and training.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;These roles will enable you to develop your clinical practice alongside colleagues who also have skills and qualifications in non-medical prescribing and other areas.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for Community Mental Health Nurses who are interested in developing their skills, who can work well within a team and with colleagues and professionals from other agencies eg schools and who will bring ideas and skills to the team&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The service covers the whole of East Sussex across the three Community teams and you will develop and maintain strong links with your ADHD colleagues and the rest of the CAMHS teams including psychiatry. You will hold a caseload of young people at all stages on the pathway, and will join colleagues in regular team meetings, supervision and reflective practice sessions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;These are permanent posts and are part of a wider, well established nursing discipline within the county where professional development and innovative work is actively encouraged.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants wanting part time posts will be considered&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We strongly encourage informal discussions before applying, please contact Sue Davies Service Manager for East Sussex ADHD Service on 07786398544 or Kate Mencner, Lead Nurse on 07471 217229&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameSue DaviesJob titleService ManagerEmail addresssue.davies1@sussexpartnership.nhs.ukTelephone number07786398544&lt;/p&gt;
